{{unreferenced|date=December 2014}} {{Infobox song contest entry | song = {{flagicon|Switzerland}} "Amour on t'aime" | image = | caption = | year = 1982 | country = Switzerland | artist = [[Arlette Zola]] | as = | with = | language = French | languages = | composer = Alain Morisod | lyricist = Pierre Alain | conductor = Joan Amils | place = 3rd | points = 97 | lyrics = [http://www.diggiloo.net/?1982ch from Diggiloo Thrush] | prev = Io senza te | prev_link = Io senza te | next = Io così non ci sto | next_link = Io così non ci sto }} '''"Amour on t'aime"''' (Love, we love you) is the song which represented Switzerland in the [[Eurovision Song Contest 1982]], staged in [[Harrogate]], [[United Kingdom]]. It was performed by [[Arlette Zola]] and sung in [[French language|French]].
It had performed 7th on the night, following [[Finland]]'s [[Kojo (singer)|Kojo]] singing "[[Nuku pommiin]]" and preceding [[Cyprus]]'s [[Anna Vissi]] with "[[Mono I Agapi]]". At the close of the voting, it had received 97 points and placed 3rd in a field of 18, behind the entries of [[Germany]] and [[Israel]].
It was succeeded as Swiss representative at the [[Eurovision Song Contest 1983|1983 contest]] by [[Mariella Farré]] with "[[Io così non ci sto]]".
