'''Aviation Club de France''' was a [[gambling]] club in central [[Paris]], [[France]].
The club opened in 1907 and was widely regarded as a classic gambling site.<ref>[http://www.aviationclubdefrance.com/home_uk.html ] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100109220525/http://www.aviationclubdefrance.com/home_uk.html |date=January 9, 2010 }}</ref> In 2005, the [[Grand Prix de Paris]] leg of the [[World Poker Tour]] took place at the Aviation Club.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pokerdb.thehendonmob.com/circuit.php?a=e&n=WPT&s=5 |title=World Poker Tour 5: Hendon Mob Poker Database |website=Pokerdb.thehendonmob.com |date=2014-02-19 |accessdate=2015-12-24}}</ref>
The main games played at the Aviation Club were: [[baccarat]], [[poker]] and [[backgammon]].{{fact|date=December 2015}}
The club was closed in 2014, after a raid by the police,<ref>[http://www.pokernews.com/news/2014/09/police-raid-aviation-club-de-france-paris-19305.htm Aviation Club de France Raided By Police in Paris; 12 People Taken Into Custody] ''pokernews.com'', September 16, 2014. Retrieved May 1, 2015.</ref> and placed in liquidation in February 2015.<ref>[http://www.pokerlistings.com/historic-aviation-club-de-france-closed-for-good-13928 Historic Aviation Club de France Closed For Good], ''Poker Listings'', February 20, 2015. Retrieved May 1, 2015.</ref>
