{{more citations needed|date=January 2011}} {{Infobox company |name = Azot Public Limited Company |logo = Azot logo.gif |logo_size = 200px |type = [[Public Limited Company]] |genre = |foundation = 1962 |founder = Council of Ministers (Ukrainian SSR) |location_country = [[Ukraine]] |location_city = [[Cherkasy]] |location = <!--modifies "Headquarters" entry--> |origins = |key_people = |area_served = |industry = [[Chemical industry]] |products = [[Fertilizer#Inorganic fertilizer (synthetic fertilizer)|Nitrogen Fertilizers]] |services = |revenue = |operating_income = |net_income = |num_employees = more than 6000 |parent = [[Ostchem Holding]] |divisions = |subsid = |owner = |slogan = |homepage = http://azot.cherkassy.net |dissolved = |footnotes = }} '''Azot''' is the biggest manufacturer of nitrogen fertilizers in Ukraine.{{peacock term|date=November 2017}} The chemical plant, better known as Cherkaskyi Azot, is part of bigger chemical holding [[Ostchem Holding]] which unites several other chemical plants in [[Ukraine]] and some former Soviet republics that specialize in manufacturing of fertilizers.
The construction of this plant began in 1962 and on March 14, 1965 the first batch of fertilizers was produced. The plant's name, Azot, means [[nitrogen]].
Now{{when|date=November 2017}} "Azot" has 43 subdivisions which are located on {{convert|500|hectare|acre|abbr=on}} at the southern outskirts of [[Cherkasy]] city. "Azot" employs more than 6000 people.<ref>http://azot.cherkassy.net/content/news/history.php</ref>
Fully loaded, the facilities allow to produce up to 3 million tonnes of fertilizers per year.{{citation needed|date=November 2017}} The plant produces quality production which allows them to export it to Asia, Europe and America.
The products include:<ref>http://azot.cherkassy.net/production/page.php</ref> * Aqua Ammonia Commercial * Commercial Liquid Ammonia * Ammonium Nitrate 34,4% N. * Liquid carbon Dioxide * Ion-exchange resins - Annionite AV-17-8 * Ion-exchange resins - Cation Ku-2-8 * Caprolactam Crystalline * UREA 46% N * UAN 32%N * Ammonium Sulphate
